  RFC8556 [label="RFC8556
Multicast VPN Using Bit Index Explicit
Replication (BIER)
2019", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="The Multicast Virtual Private Network (MVPN) specifications require the use of multicast tunnels (P-tunnels) that traverse a service provider's backbone network.  The P-tunnels are used for carrying multicast traffic across the backbone.  A variety of P-tunnel types are supported.  Bit Index Explicit Replication (BIER) is a new architecture that provides optimal multicast forwarding through a multicast domain, without requiring intermediate routers to maintain any per-flow state or to engage in an explicit tree-building protocol.  This document specifies the protocol and procedures that allow MVPN to use BIER as the method of carrying multicast traffic over a service provider's backbone network.", style=filled, fillcolor=green, fontsize=18, penwidth=3, fontweight=bold]; 

